## What

The perspective tab bar sits at the top of the main content area, above the active view (board or grid). The user expects universal spatial nav: from anywhere in the window layer, pressing `k` enough times eventually lands on a perspective tab. No view should trap focus.

Today, `ScopedPerspectiveTab` in `kanban-app/ui/src/components/perspective-tab-bar.tsx` uses `CommandScopeProvider` only — no FocusScope, no spatial entry. Beam test has zero perspective-tab candidates.

This task is the GENERIC version — ensure perspective tabs are reachable from the board, the grid, and any future view. Inspector excluded (modal layer).

### TDD — failing tests

Under `kanban-app/e2e/spatial-nav-perspective.e2e.ts`:

```ts
describe("perspective bar reachable from all views", () => {
  it("k from top-row card in the board moves focus to the active perspective tab", async () => {
    await openBoardFixture();
    await click(cardEl("card-1-1"));
    await keyboard("k"); // already in top row
    const focused = await getFocusedMoniker();
    expect(focused).toMatch(/^perspective:/);
  });

  it("k from top-row cell in a grid moves focus to the active perspective tab", async () => {
    await openTagsGridFixture();
    await click(cellEl(0, 0));
    await keyboard("k");
    const focused = await getFocusedMoniker();
    expect(focused).toMatch(/^perspective:/);
  });

  it("h/l between perspective tabs in the same bar", async () => {
    await clickPerspectiveTab("Default");
    await keyboard("l");
    const focused = await getFocusedMoniker();
    expect(focused).toMatch(/^perspective:/);
    expect(focused).not.toBe("perspective:Default");
  });

  it("j from an active perspective tab moves into the active view", async () => {
    await clickPerspectiveTab("Default");
    await keyboard("j");
    const focused = await getFocusedMoniker();
    // Either a card (board) or a cell (grid) — at least some non-perspective target
    expect(focused).not.toMatch(/^perspective:/);
  });
});
```

### Approach

1. Change `ScopedPerspectiveTab` to wrap in `FocusScope` (renderContainer=false, showFocusBar=false) with `moniker("perspective", perspective.id)`.
2. Inner `PerspectiveTab` root `<div>` attaches the FocusScope elementRef via `FocusScopeElementRefContext` — the same ref-sharing pattern as grid cells, table rows, and LeftNav buttons.

### Acceptance

- [ ] All 4 E2E tests pass reliably
- [ ] Existing perspective rename / context-menu behaviors unchanged
- [ ] No regression in other nav tests

